h2. HTML <embed> Tag

The <embed> tag defines %{color:yellow}a container for an external resource%, such as a web page, a picture, a media player, or a plug-in application.


<pre>
<embed type="image/jpg" src="pic_trulli.jpg" width="300" height="200">
<embed type="text/txt" src="4.audio.txt" width="500" height="200">
</pre>


h3. Warning
* Most browsers no longer support Java Applets and Plug-ins.
* ActiveX controls are no longer supported in any browsers.
* The support for Shockwave Flash has also been turned off in modern browsers.

h3. Suggestion

To display a picture, it is %{color:yellow}better to use the <code><img></code>% tag.

To display HTML, it is %{color:yellow}better to use the <code><iframe></code>% tag.

To display video or audio, it is %{color:yellow}better to use the <video> and <audio>% tags

    